Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Pop the @Pork and Oregano Sausage{4} on a #baking tray{} and roast on the middle shelf of your oven until golden brown and cooked through, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through. Remove and keep covered once cooked.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. The sausages are cooked when they are no longer pink in the middle.

In the meantime, roughly chop the @Flat Leaf Parsley{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). Pick the @Rosemary{1}(leaves picked and roughly chopped, stalks reserved) from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks). Drain and rinse the @Cannellini Beans{1}(drained and rinsed) in a #sieve{}. Pop 1/4 of the beans into a small #bowl{} and mash gently with a #fork{}. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @Olive Oil{2} in a large #saucepan{} on medium-high heat. When hot, add the @Diced Chicken Breast{260%g}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and cook until it starts to brown, ~{5-6%minutes}, stirring occasionally.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling chicken and its packaging.

Add the @Tomatoes{1}(finely chopped), beans (whole and mashed), @Chicken Stock Paste{10}, @Water{100%ml} and half the rosemary to the pan. Season with salt and pepper. Bring up to the boil then reduce the heat and simmer gently until thickened, ~{10-12%minutes}.

While the cassoulet cooks, cut the @Ciabatta{1} in half. Put the garlic, the remaining rosemary and the olive oil into a small bowl, mix well then spread the garlicky mix on top of each cut side. Pop them onto one side of the sausage baking tray and bake until golden, ~{5-6%minutes}. Then remove from the oven.

In the meantime, heat a drizzle of oil in a medium #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Add the @Chorizo{60%g} and fry until it starts to brown on the outside, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add the @Panko Breadcrumbs{25%g} to the chorizo and fry, stirring regularly, until they are lightly toasted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> TIP: Watch them like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Once cooked, remove the chorizo crumbs to a bowl, add the parsley and mix well.

Once the cassoulet is cooked, remove from the heat, taste and season with more salt and pepper if needed.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Spoon the chicken and bean cassoulet into #bowls{}, top with the sausages and finish by sprinkling the chorizo-parsley crumbs all over. Serve with the rosemary garlic bread on the side and tuck in. Enjoy!